\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## **Critical Architecture Decisions:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **1. Three-Tier State Management:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Your understanding is correct - it's a **hybrid approach**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Flink State (Hot)**: Active encounters, 7-30 day window, O(1) lookups
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **FHIR Store (Warm)**: Complete longitudinal clinical record
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Neo4j (Graph)**: Relationship-based reasoning, care networks, cohorts
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **2. First-Time Patient Flow:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The key innovation is the **async lookup pattern**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```java
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 if (patientState.value() == null) \{
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0// Parallel async lookups with 500ms timeout
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0fhirLookup = fhirClient.getPatient(patientId);
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0graphLookup = neo4jDriver.queryGraph(patientId);
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0if (both return 404) \uc0\u8594  truly new patient
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0if (either returns data) \uc0\u8594  hydrate from history
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0if (timeout) \uc0\u8594  initialize empty, hydrate async later
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \}
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 This prevents blocking the stream while ensuring you catch patients who exist in your system but are new to Flink's state.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **3. State Evolution Pattern:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Notice the **progressive enrichment**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - T0: Minimal context (just demographics)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - T1-T4: Each event adds layers (vitals \uc0\u8594  labs \u8594  meds \u8594  diagnoses)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - T5: State flush to persistent stores
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - TTL: Keep for 7 days for readmission correlation
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **4. Data Store Responsibilities:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Each store serves a specific purpose:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **FHIR**: "What happened clinically?" (observations, conditions, medications)\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Neo4j**: "How are things connected?" (care teams, pathways, risk cohorts)\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **ClickHouse**: "What are the trends?" (aggregations, population analytics)\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Flink State**: "What's happening right now?" (streaming enrichment)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## **Performance Considerations:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The **async lookup with timeout** is critical:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Most events hit Flink state only (microsecond latency)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - First-time patients trigger external lookups (500ms budget)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Timeout fallback prevents stream blocking
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Later backfill hydrates missed history
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## **Implementation Gotchas:**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. **Patient Matching**: Use PMI (Patient Master Index) to catch transfers/duplicates
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. **State Size**: Circular buffers for vitals prevent unbounded growth
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. **TTL Strategy**: 7 days post-discharge balances readmission context vs. memory
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 4. **Checkpoint Impact**: Large states need incremental checkpoints
\f1\fs24 \
